SM121 (DGX Spark GB10) shared memory fix for cutlass_moe_fp4 / nvfp4_blockwise_moe

Problem:
  Both SM120 (RTX 5090, RTX PRO 6000 Blackwell) and SM121 (DGX Spark GB10)
  provide only 99 KiB (101376 bytes) of shared memory per thread block.
  The 228 KiB figure that's often cited for "Blackwell" belongs to SM100
  (B200), not SM12x — per CUTLASS maintainer @depaulmillz in
  NVIDIA/cutlass#3144.

  CUTLASS's run_fp4_blockwise_scaled_group_mm_sm120() path in
  nvfp4_blockwise_moe.cuh uses Pingpong schedule + StageCountAutoCarveout,
  which together request exactly 102400 bytes (100 KiB) of mainloop
  SMEM — just 1 KiB over the 99 KiB device budget. The CUDA runtime then
  fails with a device-side assert at line 78 whenever the triton or
  cutlass MoE runner dispatches to cutlass_moe_fp4 for NVFP4 weights.

  Confirmed trigger on DGX Spark: any NVFP4 model (Qwen3-235B-A22B-NVFP4,
  GLM-4.7-NVFP4, Qwen3.5-397B-A17B-NVFP4, etc.) run with
  moe_runner_backend=triton or =cutlass under SGLang v0.5.10.

Fix:
  Switch from KernelPtrArrayTmaWarpSpecializedPingpong to the non-pingpong
  KernelPtrArrayTmaWarpSpecialized schedule. Pingpong duplicates mainloop
  and epilogue buffers across two persistent math warp groups; the
  non-pingpong schedule uses only one math warp group plus a producer
  warp for TMA loads, eliminating that duplication. The savings are
  several KiB — well more than the 1 KiB needed to fit inside 99 KiB.

  Stages are explicitly set to StageCount<2>. Warp-specialized schedules
  require at least 2 pipeline stages to have anything to overlap between
  producer (TMA) and consumer (compute) warps; StageCount<1> is NOT a
  valid combination and CUTLASS rejects it at compile time with an SFINAE
  error on CollectiveBuilder::CollectiveOp. This was confirmed empirically
  on 2026-04-11 — an earlier variant of this patch used StageCount<1>
  and failed nvrtc JIT compile with "incomplete type" errors on every
  GemmKernel reference downstream.

  The ThreadBlockShape<_128, _128, _128> is unchanged — TMA descriptor
  validation allows stage/schedule changes but rejects M/N reduction.

  This follows the same general approach TensorRT-LLM merged in PR #12141
  (2026-03-18) for the analogous fp4_gemm_template.h path on SM121, though
  their fix operates on a different layer of the CUTLASS stack.

Refs:
  - https://github.com/NVIDIA/cutlass/issues/3144
      Root cause. Contains the verbatim SMEM numbers above
      (228 KiB SM100 vs 99 KiB SM120/121, 102400/101376 failure case).
  - https://github.com/NVIDIA/TensorRT-LLM/pull/12141
      Reference fix from NVIDIA maintainers — same StageCount<1> +
      non-pingpong approach applied to the TRT-LLM FP4 GEMM path.
  - https://github.com/sgl-project/sglang/pull/20012
      JIT migration: the target file moved from sgl-kernel/csrc/moe/
      to python/sglang/jit_kernel/csrc/moe/.

Upstream source: sgl-project/sglang tag v0.5.10

--- a/python/sglang/jit_kernel/csrc/moe/nvfp4_blockwise_moe.cuh
+++ b/python/sglang/jit_kernel/csrc/moe/nvfp4_blockwise_moe.cuh
@@ -289,7 +289,12 @@
   // Architecture definitions
   using ArchTag = cutlass::arch::Sm120;
   using OperatorClass = cutlass::arch::OpClassBlockScaledTensorOp;
-  using StageCountType = cutlass::gemm::collective::StageCountAuto;
+  // SM120/121 both have 99 KiB (101376 B) SMEM/block — not 228 KiB.
+  // Default Pingpong + auto-stages requests 100 KiB → 1 KiB over budget.
+  // StageCount<2> is the minimum for warp-specialized schedules (producer
+  // + consumer pipelining needs >= 2 stages); StageCount<1> was tried and
+  // fails CUTLASS SFINAE at template instantiation time.
+  using StageCountType = cutlass::gemm::collective::StageCount<2>;
   using ThreadBlockShape = Shape<_128, _128, _128>;
   // on the tile size

@@ -327,9 +332,8 @@
       ElementAccumulator,
       ThreadBlockShape,
       ClusterShape,
-      cutlass::gemm::collective::StageCountAutoCarveout<static_cast<int>(
-          sizeof(typename CollectiveEpilogue::SharedStorage))>,
-      cutlass::gemm::KernelPtrArrayTmaWarpSpecializedPingpong>::CollectiveOp;
+      StageCountType,
+      cutlass::gemm::KernelPtrArrayTmaWarpSpecialized>::CollectiveOp;

   using GemmKernel = cutlass::gemm::kernel::GemmUniversal<ProblemShape, CollectiveMainloop, CollectiveEpilogue>;

